{
    "name": "Giant Isopod",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any ocean<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or scuttle (3\u201320)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Curl (Ex)</b> As a standard action, a giant isopod can curl into a ball, increasing its natural armor bonus by +2 but preventing it from taking any move actions. Uncurling is also a standard action."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Giant isopods are carnivorous scavengers that scour the ocean\u2019s floor. They vaguely resemble the common wood louse in appearance, though they can grow to be up to 2-1/2 feet long and weigh nearly 4 pounds. Their unusual size and insectile appearance cause many humanoids to be wary of them, despite their relative harmlessness."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This many-legged crustacean is the size of a sewer rat, its body protected by several thick shell-like plates.</i>",
